-- Lionel Messi’s Argentina to Play Brazil in New Jersey Match on June 9
-- B y   S c o t t   S o s h n i c k
-- 2012-01-10T16:38:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/messi-s-argentina-to-play-brazil-in-soccer-exhibition-june-9-in-new-jersey.html
Argentina ’s national soccer team
will play an exhibition game against  Brazil  on June 9 at  MetLife (MET) 
Stadium in  East Rutherford ,  New Jersey .  Brazil is the sixth-ranked team in the world, while
Argentina, led by  Lionel Messi , who yesterday was named soccer’s
best player for a record third consecutive time, is 10th,
according to  FIFA , the sport’s international governing body.  Argentina this year also will play exhibitions against
 Saudi Arabia ,  Switzerland  and  Germany , according to a statement
on the national team’s website. It didn’t say which players
would participate.  Mark Lamping, chief executive officer of the company that
oversees MetLife Stadium, declined to comment. The stadium also
will host the 2014  Super Bowl ,  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
